{
  "doc_id": "20245",
  "text": "3. Transcription factories. In mammalian cell, transcribed genes located on different chromosomes come together in space in the context of transcription factories -nuclear foci that contain proteins necessary for transcription [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . It has been proposed that there exists a direct correlation between spatial proximity of chromosomal loci in the nucleus and the frequency of chromosomal translocations, commonly observed in human cancers, between those loci [CITATION_3] . Transcription-induced association of genes located on different chromosomes might contribute to this process [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . Trans interactions have been also been proposed to play a role in regulation of transcription in mouse olfactory system ( [CITATION_7] ; but see [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] ).",
